The uncovered gap is in `baseline-fairness`: it verifies that a successful rerun record exists and uses the same metric, but not that the rerun actually confirms the claimed direction. I’m hardening this conservatively—only when direction is explicit or the metric has an unambiguous conventional direction—and adding both a clean confirmation control and a claim-invalidating failed-confirmation case.
